  "prompt": "How much scholarship can I get for applying ms in USA through gre?",
  "response": "The amount of scholarship you can receive for applying to a Master's program in the USA based on your GRE scores can vary widely depending on several factors, including:\n\n1. **University and Program**: Different universities and programs have different funding levels. Highly ranked institutions and competitive programs may offer more substantial scholarships.\n\n2. **GRE Scores**: While GRE scores are one factor in the scholarship decision, they are typically considered alongside your overall application, including academic records, letters of recommendation, personal statements, and relevant experience. Higher GRE scores can enhance your chances of receiving a scholarship.\n\n3. **Type of Scholarship**: There are various types of scholarships available, such as merit-based, need-based, departmental scholarships, and specific program scholarships. Merit-based scholarships are often awarded based on academic achievement and standardized test scores.\n\n4. **International Student Status**: Scholarships available to international students may differ from those offered to domestic students. Some universities have specific funds available for international students.\n\n5. **Availability of Funds**: The budget and funding availability of the specific department or university can also impact how much scholarship money is available.\n\nScholarships can range from a few hundred dollars to full tuition coverage plus a stipend for living expenses. It's best to research specific programs you're interested in and check their scholarship offerings and eligibility requirements. Additionally, reaching out to the admissions office or the financial aid office of the universities can provide more tailored information.",
